  <Method>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_124613.jpg">Saute onion in pan with olive oil until lightly browned, set aside.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_125423.jpg">In a bowl, add ground beef, baking soda, salt, pepper, MSG, bread crumbs, onion, garlic, parsley, rosemary, thyme, garlic powder and onion powder.</Step>
    <Step image="">Combine ingredients to form a loose loaf.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_125829.jpg">Using a two ounce scoop, form the meat ball.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_130506.jpg">Assemble the formed meat balls.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_132017.jpg">Preheat a heavy bottom skillet, add the meatballs and brown them, turning as needed.</Step>
    <Step image="">Remove the meatballs from the pan and set aside.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_132022.jpg">Add flour to the render beef fat in the pan and cook the flour to create a brown roux.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_155959.jpg">Add beef stock to the pan, whisking to combine with the roux. Raise the heat until the mixture begins to boil and then reduce to simmer.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_160923.jpg">Add meatballs to simmering gravy.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_160927.jpg">In a large sauce pan, melt butter over low heat and then stir in rice to coat.</Step>
    <Step image="">Add enough wdter to pan with rice until the rice is covered such that when the tip of your finger is touching the rice, the water is just at the first joint of your finger.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_162735.jpg">Bring the rice to a boil and reduce to a simmer until all the water is absorbed.</Step>
    <Step image="">Adjust the seasoning.</Step>
    <Step image="Meatballs%20and%20Rice_20250419_162918.jpg">Serve meatballs over the rice.</Step>
  </Method>
